<Base title="Privacy Policy — Queendom" description="Privacy policy for the Queendom puzzle game app">
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 26, 2026</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Queendom ("the App") is a puzzle game developed by Cambay Studio. This
    privacy policy explains how we handle your information.
  </p>

  <h2>Data We Collect</h2>

  <h3>Game Data (stored locally on your device)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Player profile (username, avatar)</li>
    <li>Game progress and statistics</li>
    <li>Saved game state</li>
    <li>User preferences (theme, sound settings)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This data is stored only on your device and is never transmitted to our
    servers.
  </p>

  <h3>Advertising Data</h3>
  <p>We use Google AdMob to show ads. AdMob may collect:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Device identifiers (advertising ID)</li>
    <li>IP address (for approximate location/ad relevance)</li>
    <li>App usage data (ad interactions)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    For more information, see
    <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank"
      >Google's Privacy Policy</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h3>iOS App Tracking</h3>
  <p>
    On iOS, we request permission via App Tracking Transparency before
    collecting any tracking data for personalized ads. If you decline, ads will
    still be shown but will not be personalized.
  </p>

  <h2>Data We Do NOT Collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Personal information (name, email, phone)</li>
    <li>Location data</li>
    <li>Contacts or photos</li>
    <li>Payment information</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Service</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Privacy Policy</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Google AdMob</td>
        <td>Advertising</td>
        <td
          ><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Link</a
          ></td
        >
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Google UMP</td>
        <td>GDPR consent</td>
        <td
          ><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Link</a
          ></td
        >
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Queendom is a family-friendly puzzle game. We set ad content rating to "G"
    (General audiences). We do not knowingly collect personal information from
    children under 13.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    All game data is stored locally on your device. Uninstalling the app removes
    all data.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Rights</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You can reset all game data by clearing app storage</li>
    <li>You can delete all data by uninstalling the App</li>
    <li>You can opt out of personalized ads via your device settings</li>
    <li>On iOS, you can deny tracking via App Tracking Transparency prompt</li>
    <li>EU users can manage consent via the in-app consent form</li>
    <li>You may request data deletion by <a href="/contact/">contacting us</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected in the
    "Last updated" date above.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For questions about this privacy policy,
    <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
